Comparison of the two procedures showed that the two-tube PCR was superior to the one-tube RT-PCR with respect to sensitivity and signal detection. Addition of random hexadeoxyribonucleotide (pd(N)6) for RT-priming to the one-tube RT-PCR system improved the sensitivity however, detection of cytokine signals did not lead to the sensitivity obtained in the two-tube system (Fig. 5
). In all the cytokines systems, the two-tube system yielded the best sensitivity, shown by the lowest C
T values.
